cs.FL, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with formal theory and query languages for streaming data, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The use of data registers and numerical aggregates also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The logical characterization of the streamable regular transductions using MSO-definable transformations suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO), while the study of closure properties suggests a connection to complexity theory (cs.CC).
